{"id": "EUVD-2024-50509", "enisaUuid": "0efc89de-d52d-3235-94af-dcbc165c5038", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nnvme-multipath: defer partition scanning\n\nWe need to suppress the partition scan from occuring within the\ncontroller's scan_work context. If a path error occurs here, the IO will\nwait until a path becomes available or all paths are torn down, but that\naction also occurs within scan_work, so it would deadlock. Defer the\npartion scan to a different context that does not block scan_work.", "datePublished": "2024-11-21T18:17:09", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-20T08:51:40", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:N/A:H", "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/60de2e03f984cfbcdc12fa552f95087c35a05a98", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/4a57f42e5ed42cb8f1beb262c4f6d3e698939e4e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a91b7eddf45afeeb9c5ece11dddff5de0921b00f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/1f021341eef41e77a633186e9be5223de2ce5d48", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2024-53093", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/01/msg00001.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2024-53093"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.06, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "11dc11cc-e195-397e-83b4-59b68389a864", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "2f86b7c5-d4bf-3745-b798-34a072e5995e", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12"}, {"id": "3554e022-2a7a-3a6d-8334-32378d2e5522", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32acab3181c7053c775ca128c3a5c6ce50197d7f <4a57f42e5ed42cb8f1beb262c4f6d3e698939e4e"}, {"id": "38eb4a6e-629f-352c-b0f6-fec1c71fc9f9", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.11.9"}, {"id": "7d053754-d247-37a2-922a-d93f747782fd", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "32acab3181c7053c775ca128c3a5c6ce50197d7f <a91b7eddf45afeeb9c5ece11dddff5de0921b00f"}, {"id": "818232ba-411d